<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="V7" checkit-title="Basis of a subspace">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the subspace <me>W=\operatorname{span} \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
-1 \\
0 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
2 \\
-2 \\
4
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
-4 \\
5 \\
-5
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
3 \\
-6 \\
3
\end{array}\right] \right\}.</me>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li> Explain how to find a basis of <m>W</m>.</li>
        <li> Explain how to find the dimension of <m>W</m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <p><me>\operatorname{RREF}\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; -1 &amp; 2 &amp; 0 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; -4 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; -2 &amp; 5 &amp; -6 \\
-3 &amp; 4 &amp; -5 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me></p>
     <ol>
          <li>A basis of <m>W</m> is <m>\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
-1 \\
0 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
2 \\
-2 \\
4
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
-4 \\
5 \\
-5
\end{array}\right] \right\}</m>.</li>
          <li>The dimension of <m>W</m> is <m>3</m>.</li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
